{{Top}}
{{Otheruses|Blaster}}
{{Quote|Hokey religions and ancient weapons are no match for a good blaster at your side, kid.|[[Han Solo]], to [[Luke Skywalker]] on the supposed advantages of a blaster over a lightsaber|<ref name="Episode 4">{{Film|IV}}</ref>}}
[[File:Blasters-SWE.png|thumb|right|300px|Blasters came in many shapes and sizes.]]
A '''blaster''',<ref name="Cross">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref> also called a '''gun''',<ref name="Rookies">{{TCW|Rookies (episode)}}</ref> was any type of ranged weapon that fired bolts of intense [[plasma]] or [[Particle beam|particle-based energy]], often mistaken for [[laser]]s.

==Description==
{{Quote|Oh, ''Anakin!'' Thank goodness. Are you alright?''"<br />"''Besides the fact you're waving a blaster around, Padmé, I'm fine.|[[Padmé Amidala Naberrie|Padmé Amidala]] and [[Anakin Skywalker]]|<ref name="The Incident, Part 2">{{IDWAdventuresCite-2020|issue=6|story=The Incident, Part 2}}</ref>}}
Operating under the same principles as [[laser]] weaponry and firing at least partially by means of magnetic induction, blasters converted energy-rich gas,<ref name="Cross" /> such as [[tibanna]] gas,<ref name="HC 54">{{HelmetCollectionCite|54|Databank A-Z}}</ref> to a glowing particle beam that could pierce and melt through targets.<ref name="Cross" /> The gas was activated by a [[power cell]] and converted to [[plasma]], released from a magnetic bottle effect which fired through collimating components as a coherent bolt of energy,<ref name="CVD NE">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref> called a "blaster bolt," which carried the shard of energy to the target.<ref name="Vengence">''[[The High Republic: Path of Vengeance]]''</ref>

Blasters came in a variety of sizes and shapes, including [[stun blaster]]s,<ref name="Gadgets and Gear">''[[Gadgets and Gear]]''</ref> [[blaster pistol]]s, [[blaster rifle]]s,<ref name="Episode I">{{Film|I}}</ref> [[reconfigurable blaster]]s,<ref name="Solo">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref> [[Scattergun|scatterblasters]],<ref name="Star Wars 4">[[Star Wars (2015) 4|''Star Wars'' (2015) 4]]</ref> [[shock blaster]]s,<ref name="CVD NE">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref> [[ion blaster]]s,<ref name="USW">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> [[ion rifle]]s,<ref name="SC 102">{{SkeletonCrew|Way, Way Out Past The Barrier}}</ref> [[percussive cannon]]s,<ref name="TFA VD" /> [[heavy repeater cannon]]s,<ref name="R1 VG" /> [[repeating blaster]]s,<ref name="USW" /> and [[blaster cannon]]s.<ref name="CV">[[Star Wars: Complete Vehicles (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Vehicles'' (2016)]]</ref>

Blaster artillery could also be attached on [[droid]]s<ref name="SWEdroi">{{SWE|technology|droideka|droideka}}</ref> and vehicles.<ref name="swe">{{SWE|technology|snowspeeder|snowspeeder}}</ref> They could deliver variable levels of damage intensity, from [[stun]] to kill settings.<ref name="SWEbla">{{SWE|technology|blasters|blasters}}</ref> Several blasters like the [[Satine's Lament]]<ref name="USW" /> and the [[Glie-44 blaster pistol]] were named after individuals.<ref name="yak_face">{{Twitter|starwars|status/700851618946764800|Star Wars|quote=@yak_face Yes.|archivedate=20190723185124}}</ref> Several blasters were also hybrids with [[melee weapon]]s like the [[bo-rifle]],<ref name="Rebels: The Visual Guide">''[[Star Wars Rebels: The Visual Guide]]''</ref> the [[blaster spear]],<ref name="Water War">{{TCW|Water War}}</ref> and [[Ketsu's staff]].<ref name="BS">{{Rebels|Blood Sisters}}</ref>

[[File:Gar-Saxon-Shatterpoint.png|thumb|left|250px|Mandalorian [[Gar Saxon]] using his [[Galar-90 rifle]] in combat]]
Blaster bolts could also deliver a variable degree of concussive force on impact, which could potentially cause additional damage around the impact area, depending on the hardness level and density of the target. As such, some blaster hits could cause [[Blood|bleeding]] instead of burning, or could do both, with the force of the impact being enough to rupture organs and break bone, especially if the target is armored in any way. Despite their blazing concussive blasts, those ranged energized particle weapons could be countered by [[magnetic seal]]s and [[deflector shield]]s. The blade of a [[lightsaber]] could also deflect incoming blaster bolts.<ref name="SWEbla" /> In the [[Royal Naboo Security Forces|Security Forces]] of [[Naboo]], some blasters were equipped with [[ascension gun]]s.<ref name="SWEpan">{{SWE|characters|captainpanaka|Captain Panaka}}</ref> Some blasters could fire low-powered training bolts characterized by their orange [[color]].<ref name="Vision trivia">{{SW|url=series/star-wars-rebels/vision-of-hope-trivia-gallery|text="Vision of Hope" Trivia Gallery}}</ref>

Blaster bolts left marks on skin known as blaster burns.<ref name="Aldhani">{{Andor|Aldhani (episode)}}</ref> [[Dedlanite]] was a material used in the manufacture of blasters.<ref name="Chewbacca Part I">[[Chewbacca (2015) 1|''Chewbacca'' (2015) 1]]</ref> [[BlasTech Industries]] was a major manufacturer of blasters.<ref name="USW" /> A [[Trandoshan doubler]] or [[Trandoshan tripler|tripler]]<ref name="TFA VD">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> and an [[actuating module]]<ref name="Gadgets and Gear" /> increased a blaster's firepower. [[Hair trigger]]s allowed faster rates of fire.<ref name="COTR">''[[Collapse of the Republic]]''</ref> Blasters also had serial numbers on [[Snub-blaster|them]].<ref name="TFA VD" />

Blaster components included a [[stock]],<ref name="TFA VD" /> [[scope]],<ref name="BF2">''[[Star Wars Battlefront II]]''</ref> [[safety]],<ref name="TFA VD" /> [[cautionary pulser]],<ref name="SASWSTOG">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story The Official Guide]]''</ref> [[blaster power pack]],<ref name="TC">''[[Battlefront: Twilight Company]]''</ref> [[cooling unit]],<ref name="Blasters and Firearms">{{EncyclopediaCite|Blasters and Ranged Weapons}}</ref> [[barrel]],<ref name="TFA VD" /> [[barrel-shroud]],<ref name="R1 VG">''[[Star Wars: Rogue One: The Ultimate Visual Guide]]''</ref> [[glowrod]],<ref name="RebellionBegins">''[[The Rebellion Begins]]''</ref> and [[bayonet]].<ref name="COTR" />

[[File:HernanCarracedo-NoEscape-Red.png|thumb|right|300px|The red blaster bolts of Imperial blaster weaponry]]
Blaster bolts came in different colors. Red was the most common color, and was made from cheaper gas. This color was used by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]], the [[Galactic Empire]],<ref name="Graphics">''[[Star Wars Super Graphic: A Visual Guide to a Galaxy Far, Far Away]]''</ref> and the [[First Order]].<ref name="Episode VII">{{Film|VII}}</ref> Blue was used by the [[Galactic Republic]], and the [[Resistance]].<ref name="USWNE">''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''</ref> Green was used by Naboo Security Forces,<ref name="Graphics" /> and the [[Umbaran]]s, as well as the [[Imperial Starfighter Corps|Starfighter Corps]] of the Galactic Empire. This was a more expensive and more powerful type of blaster gas.<ref name="Darkness Umbara">{{TCW|Darkness on Umbara}}</ref> Yellow was used by [[Mandalorian]]s.<ref name="Graphics" /> Purple was used by the [[Nantex-class territorial defense starfighter|Geonosian Starfighters]]<ref name="Episode II">{{Film|II}}</ref> and the [[Techno Union]] [[octuptarra tri-droid]] variant on the planet [[Skako Minor]].<ref name="On the Wings of Keeradaks">{{TCW|On the Wings of Keeradaks}}</ref> Orange was used by the [[Marksman-H training remote]] and training [[Battle droid|droids]] on [[Kamino]] as a low power and non-lethal type of blaster bolt. Cyan was a low-powered version of the blue blaster bolt that was used by [[clone cadet]]s in their [[Training blaster|training]] sessions against training droids.<ref name="Aftermath">{{TBB|Aftermath (episode)}}</ref>

[[Kyber crystal]]s were normally used to power lightsabers, but could also be used to power other weapons. People had tried to make kyber [[bomb]]s and kyber blasters, and there were a few weapons like a [[lightsaber rifle]], of that kind in the [[Jedi Archives]].<ref name="Lesson">{{StoryCite|story=The Lesson (Obi-Wan & Anakin)|book=Star Wars (2020) 25|sformatted=The Lesson (Obi-Wan & Anakin)}}</ref>

[[Slugthrower]]s differed from blasters by firing [[slug]]s, solid projectiles fired at high speed.<ref name="USW" />

